
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-weis-tcp-mac-option-00.txt'>
    <title>"TCP Message Authentication Code Option", Brian Weis</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-weis-tcp-mac-option-00.txt</link>
    <description>This memo describes a TCP [RFC0793] extension to enhance security for BGP [I-D.ietf-idr-bgp4] and other TCP-based protocols requiring message authentication. It provides message authentication using a Message Authentication Code (MAC), which is a superior authentication method to the keyed MD5 method previously used. The option also includes provision for automatic generation and distribution of MAC keys. A set of MAC algorithms are specified, as well as guidance when to use each one.</description>
    <dc:date>2005-12-07T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
